KPE
public class ArrayTuple
extends AbstractTuple
implements java.io.Serializable

Implements an array-tuple where the column objects are packed together in an object array. This is an efficient implementation of the tuple interface using arrays. For convenience, the implementation extends AbstractTuple. 

   Tuple tuple = new ArrayTuple(resultSet);
creates a tuple for the given result set. An object array is used to store the elements. 
   ArrayTuple.FACTORY_METHOD.invoke(resultSet)
does the same.

Field Detail

FACTORY_METHOD

public static final Function<java.lang.Object,ArrayTuple> FACTORY_METHOD
A factory method that constructs objects of the class ArrayTuple. The function can be called with one or a list of parameters (corresponding to the two constructors of the class):
  • resultSet: a result set from which data and metadata is taken. 
           ResultSet resultSet = ...;
       Tuple t = ArrayTuple.FACTORY_METHOD.invoke(resultSet);
  • objects: a list of arguments containing the objects.
    Caution: tuple is linked (not copied). So, changes to the original variables will cause changes to the tuple! List
